Alhaji Umaru Badami, father to Governor Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri of Adamawa, is dead. Badami, 82, died on Sunday after a protracted illness, according to Mr Solomon Kumangar, Director-General, Media and Communications to the governor. He said that the octogenarian passed away around 2.30 p.m. “He was on admission at the Federal Medical Centre, Yola and was discharged yesterday only to later collapse,” Kumagar said. The deceased, a retired soldier, is survived by a wife and six children, including Governor Fintiri. Badami had been buried according to Islamic rites after funeral prayers at the Yola Central Mosque. Adamawa PDP governorship candidate promises N32,000 Minimum Wage Gulak Calls For Fintiri's Resignation Gov. Fintiri pledges vital role for traditional rulers in Adamawa Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin